_тЪая╕П Potential issue_ | _ЁЯЯа Major_

**Prevent duplicate service registrations when `AddTailwind` is called multiple times.**

If a consumer accidentally calls `AddTailwind()` more than once, `TailwindWatchService` will be registered multiple times, causing multiple watch processes to run concurrently. Use `TryAdd` methods to make the registration idempotent.



<details>
<summary>ЁЯЫбя╕П Proposed fix to prevent duplicate registrations</summary>

```diff
+using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.Extensions;
 using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;

 namespace ForgeTrust.Runnable.Web.Tailwind;

 public static class TailwindExtensions
 {
     public static IServiceCollection AddTailwind(this IServiceCollection services)
     {
         services.Configure<TailwindOptions>(_ => { });
-        services.AddSingleton<TailwindCliManager>();
-        services.AddHostedService<TailwindWatchService>();
+        services.TryAddSingleton<TailwindCliManager>();
+        services.TryAddEnumerable(ServiceDescriptor.Singleton<IHostedService, TailwindWatchService>());

         return services;
     }

     public static IServiceCollection AddTailwind(this IServiceCollection services, Action<TailwindOptions> configureOptions)
     {
         services.Configure(configureOptions);
-        services.AddSingleton<TailwindCliManager>();
-        services.AddHostedService<TailwindWatchService>();
+        services.TryAddSingleton<TailwindCliManager>();
+        services.TryAddEnumerable(ServiceDescriptor.Singleton<IHostedService, TailwindWatchService>());

         return services;
     }
 }
```

</details>

